agement factor models (SEFMs), and chatbot interaction analysis. This chapter focuses on the first iteration, personas elicitation, which proposes a data-driven persona development method (DDPDM) that utilises machine learning, precisely a k-means clustering technique. Data analysis is conducted using two datasets. Eight personas are produced from the two data analyses. The pragmatic findings from this study make two contributions to the current literature. Firstly, the proposed DDPDM uses machine learning, specifically k-means clustering, to build data-driven personas. Secondly, the persona template is designed for university students, which supports the construction of data-driven personas. Future work will cover the second and third iterations. <\\/jats:p>\",\"DOI\":\"10.4018\\/978-1-7998-5009-0.ch004\",\"type\":\"book-chapter\",\"created\":{\"date-parts\":[[2021,5,17]],\"date-time\":\"2021-05-17T12:14:04Z\",\"timestamp\":1621253644000},\"page\":\"72-113\",\"source\":\"Crossref\",\"is-referenced-by-count\":0,\"title\":\"Applications of Machine Learning in Education\",\"prefix\":\"10.4018\",\"author\":[{\"given\":\"Fatima Ali\",\"family\":\"Amer Jid Almahri\",\"sequence\":\"first\",\"affiliation\":[{\"name\":\"Brunel University London, UK\"}]},{\"given\":\"David\",\"family\":\"Bell\",\"sequence\":\"additional\",\"affiliation\":[{\"name\":\"Brunel University London, UK\"}]},{\"given\":\"Mahir\",\"family\":\"Arzoky\",\"sequence\":\"additional\",\"affiliation\":[{\"name\":\"Brunel University London, UK\"}]}],\"member\":\"2432\",\"reference\":[{\"key\":\"978-1-7998-5009-0.ch004.-1\",\"doi-asserted-by\":\"publisher\",\"DOI\":\"10.14569\\/IJACSA.2015.060712\"},{\"key\":\"978-1-7998-5009-0.ch004.-2\",\"doi-asserted-by\":\"publisher\",\"DOI\":\"10.1.1.106.1099\"},{\"key\":\"978-1-7998-5009-0.ch004.-3\",\"doi-asserted-by\":\"publisher\",\"DOI\":\"10.1145\\/1125451.1125456\"},{\"key\":\"978-1-7998-5009-0.ch004.-4\",\"doi-asserted-by\":\"publisher\",\"DOI\":\"10.1109\\/ISIIC